OL,7,F"Unfortunately, in a period of
OL,8,Feconomic hardship, where times are
OL,9,Ftough as they are now, it is always
OL,10,Fthe marginalised communities, always
OL,11,Fthe minorities, that face the
OL,12,Fattacks," he explains.
OL,14,F"We saw it in the 1920s. We sadly saw
OL,15,Fit in the 1930s. We saw it in the
OL,16,F1970s and now we see the Muslim
OL,17,Fcommunity. We see vulnerable
OL,18,Fminorities facing the attack, being
OL,19,Fblamed for economic hardship," he
OL,20,Fadded.
